{"id":91452,"title":"What 'works' in cognitive rehabilitation: opinion paper.","abstract":"This opinion paper provides a summary of some aspects of rehabilitation which seem to empower change and progress in people following brain injury according to the authors experience. It frames this within 3 factors: 1) What you do, 2) Who the brain injury survivor is, and 3) Who you are. ","date":"2014-02-07","categories":"Wounds and Injuries","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24503643","annotations":[{"name":"Physical therapy","weight":0.285378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Physical_therapy"},{"name":"Brain","weight":0.280357,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain"},{"name":"Cognition","weight":0.278001,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognition"},{"name":"Traumatic brain injury","weight":0.110498,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Traumatic_brain_injury"},{"name":"Injury","weight":0.0459474,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Injury"},{"name":"Film frame","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Film_frame"},{"name":"Cognitive rehabilitation therapy","weight":0.0156195,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cognitive_rehabilitation_therapy"},{"name":"Empowerment","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empowerment"},{"name":"Paper","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paper"}]}
